## API Conventions
- All endpoints return JSON
- Success responses use format: `{ data: T }`
- Error responses use format: `{ error: string }`
- POST returns 201 on resource creation

## Testing Requirements
- Use Vitest for all tests
- Test files: `*.test.ts` next to source files
- Test the service layer (business logic), not Express routes directly
- **Always mock the Gemini service** — never make real API calls in tests

## Environment Variables
- `OLLAMA_HOST` — Ollama server URL (default: `http://127.0.0.1:11434`)
- `OLLAMA_MODEL` — Model to use (default: `gemma3`)
- `PORT` — Server port (default: 3000)

## Do NOT
- Use `any` type
- Make real Ollama API calls in tests — always mock the LLMClient interface
- Skip error handling on route handlers
- Hardcode the model name or host URL — always use environment variables
